Mpho Raborife, News24One of the hijackers who threw a 6-year-old out of a moving car which they hijacked on Friday (Supplied). Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Johannesburg - Two men who threw a 6-year-old child out of a moving car during a hijacking were arrested on Monday, Ekurhuleni metro police said.They were arrested on Allendale Road in Midrand around 11:00 and found in possession of firearms, spokesperson Clifford Shongwe said.On Friday, they allegedly hijacked a red VW Polo Playa and threw a six-year-old child out of the window. They allegedly confessed to the crime.Their arrest was a joint operation between EMPD, Tracker and SAPS.It was not immediately clear what had happened to the child. &nbsp; 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.